                            <comment id="47235" author="ihara" created="Wed, 31 Oct 2012 19:32:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Liang,&lt;br/&gt;
This is quite interesting. What do you mean multi-mount lustre on the client?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="47201" author="liang" created="Wed, 31 Oct 2012 11:08:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;raw data of previous three tests&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http://jira.whamcloud.com/secure/attachment/12017/cpu_and_journal_log.tgz&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://jira.whamcloud.com/secure/attachment/12017/cpu_and_journal_log.tgz&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="47198" author="liang" created="Wed, 31 Oct 2012 10:33:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;again, the same environment, intel server. rerun tests with different external &amp;amp; internal journal. (2.3 only)&lt;br/&gt;
(&lt;a href=&quot;http://jira.whamcloud.com/secure/attachment/12015/smp_journal_perf_fat_intel_2.pdf&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://jira.whamcloud.com/secure/attachment/12015/smp_journal_perf_fat_intel_2.pdf&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="47197" author="liang" created="Wed, 31 Oct 2012 10:30:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;AMD server as MDS (a little slower than the intel server) which has 16 cores, rerun some tests with both 2.2 and 2.3&lt;br/&gt;
Also, because AMD server doesn&apos;t have SSD, so use 4G ramdisk ask journal device.&lt;br/&gt;
(&lt;a href=&quot;http://jira.whamcloud.com/secure/attachment/12014/smp_perf_fat_amd.pdf&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://jira.whamcloud.com/secure/attachment/12014/smp_perf_fat_amd.pdf&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="47196" author="liang" created="Wed, 31 Oct 2012 10:27:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;still use the same environment, change online CPU number of MDS and rerun some tests&lt;br/&gt;
(&lt;a href=&quot;http://jira.whamcloud.com/secure/attachment/12013/smp_perf_fat_intel_2.pdf&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://jira.whamcloud.com/secure/attachment/12013/smp_perf_fat_intel_2.pdf&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="47191" author="liang" created="Wed, 31 Oct 2012 09:04:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Here is 2.3 metadata performance demonstration for openSFS:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http://jira.whamcloud.com/secure/attachment/11805/opensfs_smp_demonstration.pdf&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://jira.whamcloud.com/secure/attachment/11805/opensfs_smp_demonstration.pdf&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Here is patched mdtest: (&lt;a href=&quot;http://jira.whamcloud.com/secure/attachment/11995/mdtest_lustre_1.8.3.tgz&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://jira.whamcloud.com/secure/attachment/11995/mdtest_lustre_1.8.3.tgz&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;user can specify stripecount of file&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;can run for mknod&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;user can use range expression to specify multiple paths&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</comment>
